structures.graph
Class DirGraph<T>

java.lang.Object
  structures.graph.DirGraph<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of object used to represent vertices.
Direct Known Subclasses:
UndirGraph
public class DirGraph<T>
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements a directed graph. An undirected grapph can be implemented by subclassing this class. Weights may be attached to the edges by subclassing the Neighbor class accordingly.

Author:
Sesh Venugopal

addEdge

public void addEdge(int vertexNumber,
                    Neighbor nbr)
Adds an edge from a given vertex (internal number) to another (neighbor). Note: If this vertex already has an edge to this neighbor, this method will return without doing anything. In other words, multiple edges are not supported.

Parameters:
vertexNumber - Internal number of vertex.
nbr - Neighbor to which edge is added.
